{
  "title": "ISic003091. Funerary inscription for two men called Silanos",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">Σιλανός</span></span></span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.)</span>  <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">Σιλανός</span></span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ἥρωες\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ἥρως\">ἥρωες</span>  <span data-text=\"ἀγαθοί\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἀγαθός\">ἀγαθοί</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">Σιλανός</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\">(vac.)</span>  <span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">Σιλανός</span>  <span data-text=\"ἥρωες\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ἥρως\">ἥρωες</span>  <span data-text=\"ἀγαθοί\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἀγαθός\">ἀγαθοί</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">ΣΙΛΑΝΟΣ</span></span></span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σιλανός\"><span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">ΣΙΛΑΝΟΣ</span></span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"ἥρωες\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ἥρως\">ΗΡΩΕΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἀγαθοί\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἀγαθός\">ΑΓΑΘΟΙ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">ΣΙΛΑΝΟΣ</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span data-text=\"Σιλανός\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Σιλανός\">ΣΙΛΑΝΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἥρωες\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"ἥρως\">ΗΡΩΕΣ</span><span data-text=\"ἀγαθοί\" data-n=\"25\" data-lemma=\"ἀγαθός\">ΑΓΑΘΟΙ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text of Giustolisi as reported in SEG</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Giustolisi proposed that it was a dedication to or invovation of the divinity Silenos, but Manganaro, and Moretti (comm in SEG) instead suggest that it is a funerary aedicola for two men called Silenos, perhaps father and son, with the designation as heroes agathoi, as is common in the later Hellenistic period.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 36.0854 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a>  </li><li> Giustolisi 1981 121-122 figs.144-148r <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001947\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001947</a>  </li><li> Manganaro 1992 500-501 no.IX <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
